    "body": "\n      <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Vehicle command script assigned to vehicles for movement, deployment, lighting, transport, or special vehicle functions. In plain language, this script is part of <strong>Vehicle Command Transport To Police Station</strong>.</p>\n      <h3>Script structure</h3>\n      <p><strong>Command/script objects:</strong> <code>VcmdToPoliceStation</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Base classes:</strong> <code>CommandScript</code></p>\n      <h3>Menu and command integration</h3>\n      <p><strong>Icons:</strong> <code>topolicestation</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Cursors:</strong> <code>topolicestation</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Commands assigned:</strong> None detected.</p>\n      <p><strong>Commands removed:</strong> <code>DummyFollow</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Commands executed:</strong> None detected.</p>\n      <h3>SDK behavior used</h3>\n      <p><strong>Action queue calls:</strong> <code>PushActions</code>, <code>PushActionExecuteCommand</code>, <code>PushActionMove</code>, <code>PushActionTurnTo</code>, <code>PushActionWait</code>, <code>PushActionFlyTo</code>, <code>PushActionLeaveCar</code>, <code>PushActionDeleteOwner</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Game namespace calls:</strong> <code>Game::IsFreeplay</code>, <code>Game::IsMultiplayer</code>, <code>Game::GetActors</code>, <code>Game::ExecuteCommand</code>, <code>Game::CollectObstaclesOnVirtualObject</code>, <code>Game::FindFreePosition</code>, <code>Game::IsSquadInVirtualObject</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Mission calls:</strong> <code>Mission::PlayHint</code></p>\n      <p><strong>Interface calls:</strong> No ScriptInterface:: calls detected.</p>\n      <h3>Assets, map objects, and dependencies</h3>\n      <p><strong>Prototype references:</strong></p><ul><li><code>mod:Prototypes/Vehicles/03</code></li></ul>\n      <p><strong>Audio references:</strong></p><ul><li><code>mod:Audio/FX/radio/1019.wav</code></li></ul>\n      <p><strong>Likely map/object name references:</strong></p><ul><li><code>VcmdToPoliceStation</code></li><li><code>policestation_helipad</code></li><li><code>policestation_entry</code></li><li><code>policestation_entry2</code></li><li><code>policestation_turnto</code></li><li><code>policestation_park01</code></li><li><code>policestation_park02</code></li><li><code>policestation_park03</code></li><li><code>policestation_park97</code></li><li><code>policestation_park98</code></li><li><code>policestation_park99</code></li><li><code>policestation_heli</code></li><li><code>policestation_spawn</code></li><li><code>topolicestation</code></li></ul>\n      <h3>Restrictions and state</h3>\n      <p><code>RESTRICT_SELFEXECUTE</code></p>\n      <h3>Integration notes</h3>\n      <ul><li>Requires matching UI command/cursor files for any custom icon or cursor names referenced by the script.</li><li>Creates or checks specific prototype paths, so prototype file names and folders must match exactly.</li><li>References audio files; missing or positional audio paths can make dispatch/feedback fail silently.</li><li>Uses dummy-command sequencing, so later steps depend on command names staying exact.</li><li>Depends on map virtual objects or VO collision checks. Map naming matters.</li><li>Uses mission/freeplay style state, timers, objectives, counters, or ticker feedback.</li><li>Controls lights or traffic light state; test day/night and return/cleanup behavior.</li><li>Manipulates passengers or transported persons; test full, empty, and multi-occupant cases.</li></ul>\n      <p><strong>Source snapshot:</strong> copied from <code>Scripts/VehicleCommand_TransportToPoliceStation.script</code> into the generated script-source snapshot. The live script in <code>Scripts</code> was not edited.</p>\n    "
